Installing erand:

Be sure you have installed the GNU Scientific Library.

sudo apt-get install libgsl0-dev

Make shell scripts executable.

chmod 755 *.sh

Next compile the programs.

./inst.sh

To de-install erand:

./deinst.sh

To see how to test erand, read TESTING.
Some of these test programs use new curses, X Windows,
and dieharder.

To read about the erand generator, read README.erand.

To see the erand website, go to https://aquila62.github.io 
